# {{†}} {{zh-alt-form|僮|tr=tóng|[[boy]]; [[young]] [[child]]|dot=;}} someone [[childish]] or [[ignorant]]
#* {{zh-x|在 後 之 侗{tóng}，敬迓 天威，嗣守 ^文、^武 大訓，無 敢 昏逾。|After them, I, the '''stupid''' one, received with reverence the dread (decree) of Heaven, and continued to keep the great instructions of Wen and Wu, not daring blindly to transgress them.|ref=Shangshu-L}}
# {{lb|zh|literary}} [[childish]]; [[unenlightened]]; [[ignorant]]
#* {{zh-x|^子 曰：「狂 而 不 直，侗{tóng} 而 不 愿，悾{kōng}悾{kōng} 而 不 信，吾 不 知 之 矣。」|The Master said, "Ardent and yet not upright, '''stupid''' and yet not attentive; simple and yet not sincere - such persons I do not understand."|ref=Analects}}
#* {{zh-x|侗{Tóng}-乎 其 無識，儻 乎 其 怠疑。|I was as a '''child''' who has no knowledge; I was extraordinarily slow and hesitating.|ref=Zhuangzi-L}}
#* {{zh-x|天 降 生 民，倥{kōng}侗{tóng} 顓蒙，恣 乎 情性，聰明 不 開。|When Tian gives birth to the masses, they are '''naive''' and '''ignorant'''. They give free reign to their desires and original natures, and their intelligence is undeveloped.|ref=Fayan-B}}
# {{†}} [[frivolous]]; [[flippant]]

